body_html: @TomorrowIsAnOtherDay I am closing since this is not a supported platform. Your options, at this juncture, are to either disable that feature in your private copy of tensorflow and rebuild, or upgrade your kernel. The comment on stackoverflow indicates that there was a backport for 2.6.32, so this might be the most viable option.

body: @TomorrowIsAnOtherDay I am closing since this is not a supported platform. Your options, at this juncture, are to either disable that feature in your private copy of tensorflow and rebuild, or upgrade your kernel. The comment on [stackoverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3261965/so-reuseport-on-linux) indicates that there was a backport for `2.6.32`, so this might be the most viable option.
